{"session_id": "26cd749e-9e51-4592-a2f3-e0a2736c7380", "task": "This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nAnalysis:\nLet me analyze the conversation chronologically:\n\n1. **Initial Setup**: User launched Claude Code from VSCode extension, confirmed it works the same as terminal.\n\n2. **Formalization Request**: User wanted to formalize the mathematical framework for inverse transformation from measurement results. Key concepts:\n   - Raw input (sx, sy) \u2208 [0, 255]\u00b2\n   - Game input (gx, gy) \u2208 [-100, 100]\n   - Switch 2 applies unwanted nonlinear 2D transformation\n   - Goal: Pico bridge correction to cancel Switch 2's transform\n\n3. **Plan Mode Phase**: Extensive exploration of codebase, defining notation:\n   - S: Switch 2 platform transform\n   - F: F-ZERO GX game transform (centering + clamp, platform-independent)\n   - T = F \u2218 S: measured transform (readings.csv)\n   - W = F: Wii transform (platform is transparent)\n   - P: Pico correction = S\u207b\u00b9 \u2218 \u03c6\n   - \u03c6: scaling from physical octagon to software octagon\n\n4. **Key Q&A Results**:\n   - Q1: Clamp [-128,-125]\u2192-125 is F-ZERO GX's processing (game-side) \u2192 allows T = F \u2218 S decomposition\n   - Q2: Value range mismatch (\u00b1125 vs \u00b1100) handling deferred as \u03c6\n\n5. **\u03c6 Definition**: User clarified:\n   - Physical stick doesn't reach full [0,255] range\n   - Problem is stick NOT at full tilt already hits software boundary \u2192 unwanted dead zone at outer edge\n   - F-ZERO GX has calibration (neutral=0%, full tilt=100%)\n   - Physical octagon a=125 (conservative safe value)\n   - \u03c6: linear scaling k = 100/125 = 4/5\n\n6. **Interactive Tool Request**: User wanted browser-based visualization tool instead of jumping to LUT generation. Start with S only, then add \u03c6 later.\n\n7. **Octagon Shape Corrections** (multiple iterations):\n   - First attempt: `|cx| \u2264 a, |cy| \u2264 a, |cx|+|cy| \u2264 140` - wrong\n   - Second: `|cx|+|cy| \u2264 a\u221a2` with vertices at (a, a(\u221a2-1)) - still wrong orientation\n   - User clarified: \"\u6b63\u516b\u89d2\u5f62\" mea", "stage": "apply", "user_decision": "approve", "edit_distance": 1.0, "user_feedback_text": "", "change_type": "docs", "turn_number": 494, "_swechat_pushback": null, "_swechat_persona": "expert_nitpicker", "_swechat_mode": "human_only", "_swechat_intent": null, "_swechat_success": "88.0", "_swechat_agent_pct": 0.0}
